<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="46" type="general">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="46">General.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="46">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mydidae" genus="Syllegomydas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllegomydas" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Syllegomydas</taxonomicName>
comprises 24 valid species distributed primarily in northern Africa, with a few species in sub-Saharan Africa (Chad, Mali, Malawi, Mozambique, Niger, Zimbabwe), as well as Afghanistan, Israel, and Spain (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Arias, J" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Real Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="176 - 179" title="Descripciones de nuevos &quot; Midasidos &quot; de Espana y del Norte de Africa" url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/bibliography/6171" volume="14" year="1914 a">Arias 1914a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Arias, J" journalOrPublisher="Arxius de l'Institut de Ciancies" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="42 - 48" title="Notas dipterologicas. II. Descripcion de un nuevo Syllegomydas del Norte de Africa y notas criticas sobre los midasidos africanus." volume="2" year="1914 b">b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="191 - 234" title="The South African Mydaidae (Diptera) as represented in the South African Museum." volume="19" year="1924">Bezzi 1924</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Seguy, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="111 - 112" title="Un Syllegomydas nouveau du Nord de l'Afrique (Dipt. Mydaidae)." volume="1941" year="1941">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Séguy">Seguy</normalizedToken>
1941
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 20" title="Contribution nouvelle a la connaissance des Mydaidae de l'Afrique tropicale." volume="27" year="1951">Bequaert 1951</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 36" title="Mydaidae palearctiques nouvelles ou peu connues." volume="37" year="1961">1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesse, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 388" title="The Mydaidae (Diptera) of Southern Africa." volume="54" year="1969">Hesse 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bowden, J" editor="Crosskey, RW" journalOrPublisher="British Museum of Natural History, London" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination="325 - 333" title="27. Family Mydidae" volumeTitle="Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region" year="1980">Bowden 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carles-Tolra, M" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa" pageId="32" pageNumber="65" pagination=": 76" title="Syllegomydas algericus (Gerstaecker): genero y especie nuevos para Europa (Diptera: Mydidae)" volume="38" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Carles-Tolrá">Carles-Tolra</normalizedToken>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
, see placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mydidae" genus="Syllegomydas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllegomydas bucciferus" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucciferus">Syllegomydas bucciferus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Séguy">Seguy</normalizedToken>
, 1928 from India in the Discussion). The subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mydidae" genus="Syllegomydas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllegomydas (Notobates)" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Notobates">Syllegomydas (Notobates)</taxonomicName>
Hesse, 1969 has been described for 2 species from southern Africa (Mozambique and Zimbabwe).
</paragraph>
